In a large mixing bowl, combine the cake mix, eggs, egg white, water and applesauce; beat on low speed for 30 seconds. Beat on medium for 2 minutes. Pour into two 9-in. baking pans coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350 degrees F for 20-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes; remove from pans to cool. In a mixing bowl, beat first five frosting ingredients until smooth. Place a cake layer on a serving plate. Spread with spreadable fruit. Top with second layer; frost top of cake.